verbose_text: In undifferentiated metazoan cells, Lin28a suppresses the maturation of let-7 miRNAs by binding to the conserved terminal loop (CTL) of the let-7 precursor (pre-let-7) and recruiting the 3 ' terminal uridyl transferase (TuTase) TuT4, which adds an oligouridine tail to the 3 ' end of pre-let-7.
evidence: Lin28a suppresses the maturation of let-7 miRNAs
